The paper discusses bibliometric measures and their application in digital libraries, specifically the NASA Astrophysics Data System. This falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the obsolescence function and citation rates, which are relevant to the field of scientometrics (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses age biases and productivity measures, which are relevant to the fields of cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR).
